Dialogue: 0,00:00:00.000,00:00:08.420,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we are performing a minimization, we are performing it over all possible functions that satisfies a certain criterion.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:08.660,00:00:12.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And these all possible functions is what we call the space.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:14.340,00:00:20.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,And here I'm going to give two examples of that space over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:22.360,00:00:28.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the first example is x is the space.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:28.080,00:00:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the space is a set of functions.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:32.080,00:00:35.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a collection of functions that satisfy a certain criterion.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:35.440,00:00:53.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,For example, is f of x between 0 and 1 such that for all i.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:53.920,00:00:54.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:55.180,00:00:58.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,So for all the i.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:58.080,00:01:07.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,We are still representing the space using a finite number of intervals.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:07.040,00:01:10.360,辉英,,0,0,0,,And these intervals are now what we call elements.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:12.040,00:01:19.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for reasons I'm going to discuss a little bit later, let's now, instead of labeling the elements as integers,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:20.080,00:01:22.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,let's label the element boundaries as integers.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:22.980,00:01:25.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,1, 2, 3, 4, etc.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:25.780,00:01:28.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,So for all the i's.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:28.080,00:01:30.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:31.660,00:01:42.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,fx is linear in x in xi minus 1 and xi.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:44.960,00:01:45.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:45.880,00:01:49.200,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is one class of functions.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:50.960,00:01:55.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,So can somebody tell me does this correspond to this case or the previous case?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:56.680,00:01:57.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,This one, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.840,00:01:58.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:58.080,00:02:02.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because I'm no longer requiring my x to be continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:04.080,00:02:04.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:05.960,00:02:13.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So for example, when i is equal to 1, when x is in x0 and x1, the function is linear like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:14.080,00:02:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,In between 1 and 2, the function can be like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:16.880,00:02:17.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:17.280,00:02:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I can have a function that is like that to approximate whatever function I want to approximate.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.760,00:02:27.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,The second case, which is the case we're going to discuss in this lecture.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:27.880,00:02:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is putting an additional constraint on the function.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:37.880,00:02:40.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,And f is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:45.480,00:02:46.240,辉英,,0,0,0,,Continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:48.040,00:02:54.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for all the i, fx is linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:56.380,00:02:56.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,In x.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:56.880,00:02:58.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,x.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:59.280,00:03:00.960,辉英,,0,0,0,,i minus 1 and xi.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:03.680,00:03:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is a space that I require the function to be not only piecewise linear but continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:10.080,00:03:16.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,So these are these kind of piecewise lines that I can draw with one stroke.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:17.440,00:03:17.940,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:20.360,00:03:20.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:21.680,00:03:26.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I claim is that this space of x satisfies a particular.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:26.280,00:03:30.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Particularly nice properties called linearity.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:30.280,00:03:32.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So what does linearity mean?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:32.280,00:03:40.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Linearity means that if I have x1 and x2 both in the space x.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:40.280,00:03:42.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:42.280,00:03:44.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So linearity.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:44.280,00:03:50.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is not linearity of the function but linearity of the function space.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:50.280,00:03:51.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:51.280,00:03:53.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's different from the linearity of the function f.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:53.280,00:03:55.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Linearity of the function f just says like f is a straight line.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:55.280,00:03:56.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you put it like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:56.280,00:03:57.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,You plot it.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:57.280,00:04:00.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,But linearity of the function space is something different.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:00.280,00:04:06.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's saying that for any pair of f1 and f2 in that linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:06.280,00:04:20.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,a1 times f1 plus a2 times f2 is also in the space for any real numbers a1 and a2.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:20.280,00:04:21.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:21.280,00:04:22.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:22.280,00:04:31.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any linear combination of any two elements in the space also belongs to the same space.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:31.280,00:04:33.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is linearity.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:35.280,00:04:37.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in this case why is the case?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:37.280,00:04:40.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why is this particular space linear?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:40.280,00:04:42.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's check it.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:43.280,00:04:45.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,First of all if I have a function like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:45.280,00:04:48.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I scale the function by a real number.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:48.280,00:04:50.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The scaled function.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:50.280,00:04:53.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's say if I scale it to a little bigger.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:53.280,00:04:56.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The scaled function would look like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:56.280,00:04:58.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course it's still continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:58.280,00:05:03.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And of course for every interval the scaled function is also linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:03.280,00:05:04.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:04.280,00:05:08.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if I have f1 in x.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:08.280,00:05:11.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,a1 times f1 is also in x.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:11.280,00:05:14.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Again if I have f2 in x.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:14.280,00:05:16.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,a2 times f2 is also in x.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:16.280,00:05:17.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is pretty much linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:17.280,00:05:22.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is because scaling is invariant.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:22.280,00:05:24.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Scaling is.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:24.280,00:05:27.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean the x is invariant to scaling.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:27.280,00:05:33.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And also if I have both a1 f1 and a2 f2 in the space.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:33.280,00:05:39.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Adding them together the sum of two continuous functions is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:39.280,00:05:43.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the sum of two linear functions is linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:43.280,00:05:44.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:44.280,00:05:47.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,a1 f1 plus a2 f2 is also.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:47.280,00:05:50.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Continuous and piecewise linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:50.280,00:05:53.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Therefore we can prove that x is a linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:53.280,00:05:57.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,By simply arguing about the properties of the functions.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:57.280,00:06:00.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,It has to satisfy.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:00.280,00:06:01.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:01.280,00:06:07.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any questions so far?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:07.280,00:06:09.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:09.280,00:06:10.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:10.280,00:06:12.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,We need to introduce the concept.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:12.280,00:06:14.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once we have a linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:14.280,00:06:16.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,A linear space is particularly nice.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:16.280,00:06:26.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,That it has this thing called a basis.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:26.280,00:06:27.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:27.280,00:06:33.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,A basis in a linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:33.280,00:06:37.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,x1 x2 all the way to xn for example.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:37.280,00:06:41.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is a basis.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:41.280,00:06:43.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is a basis.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:46.280,00:06:56.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of x.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:56.280,00:06:57.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,If and only if.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:57.280,00:06:58.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The following properties are satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:58.280,00:06:59.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So first of all.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:59.280,00:07:00.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,For any x.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:00.280,00:07:01.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,In that linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:01.280,00:07:02.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,X can be represented as a linear combination.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:02.280,00:07:03.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of these basis.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:03.280,00:07:04.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:04.280,00:07:05.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is the first property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:05.280,00:07:06.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:06.280,00:07:07.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:07.280,00:07:08.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:08.280,00:07:09.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:09.280,00:07:10.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the second property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:10.280,00:07:11.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:11.280,00:07:12.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the third property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:12.280,00:07:13.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:13.280,00:07:14.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the fourth property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:14.280,00:07:15.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the linear space.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:15.280,00:07:16.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this is the first property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:16.280,00:07:17.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:17.280,00:07:18.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another property is that.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:18.280,00:07:19.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,For any.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:19.280,00:07:20.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another property.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:20.280,00:07:21.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let me just say like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:21.280,00:07:22.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another property is that.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:22.280,00:07:23.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,This representation.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:23.280,00:07:24.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is unique.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:24.280,00:07:25.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:25.280,00:07:26.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,For any x.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:26.280,00:07:27.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:27.280,00:07:28.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,The set of.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:28.280,00:07:29.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,A i's.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:29.280,00:07:30.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:30.280,00:07:31.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,A x.
